Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @butter{20%g} from the fridge.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @garlic clove{2}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. Add the parcel to the potato tray and roast until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

In the meantime, zest and cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

Lay the @sea bass fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined large baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{}, then sprinkle over half the lemon zest.

When the potatoes have 10-15 mins left, bake the fish on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

While everything's in the oven, trim the @green beans{80%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Lower the heat to medium, then add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @capers{15%grams}.

In a small #bowl{}, mix the capers, a squeeze of lemon juice and the remaining lemon zest with the softened butter.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{} into the butter.

Once the beans are tender, add the @peas{120%grams} to the same frying pan and cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the sea bass is cooked, remove from the oven and spread the caper butter on top of the fish so it starts to melt.

Share your sea bass fillets between your plates.

Serve with your green veg, herby potatoes and some @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} for dipping.

Serve any remaining lemon wedges alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!

